Layer 1 Rules

Layer 1 must NEVER

❌ execute tools

❌ call Runtime

❌ verify permissions

❌ authorize execution

❌ perform retries

❌ generate execution plans

❌ monitor execution

Those belong to Layer 2 and Runtime.

Layer 2 – Execution Governance (Modified)
Mission

Layer 2 governs execution, not requests.

It answers one question:

"Should this specific action proposed by the Planner be executed?"

The Planner is considered untrusted.

Every proposed action must pass Layer 2 before Runtime may execute it.

