Aegis Design Principles (v2)
Layer 1 understands the request and defines execution boundaries.
Planner generates proposed actions but is never trusted to execute them.
Layer 2 deterministically validates every proposed action against identity, permissions, policies, constraints, and behavioral rules.
Runtime executes only actions explicitly approved by Layer 2.
Each layer has a single responsibility and must never assume the responsibilities of another layer.
All governance is performed before execution; all execution is performed after governance.
The trust boundary between the Planner and Runtime is enforced exclusively by Layer 2, making it the sole gateway for tool execution.